<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-27T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-27T21:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51/558: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-27T22:00:00-04:00">February
                                    27, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>103. Your 207, February 24, 4 p.m. The Department is informed by Treasury
                            Department that Secretary of Treasury is prepared to authorize for
                            monetary reserve purposes the sale to Bank Mellie Iran of $8 million
                            gold against present Iranian dollar balances, the gold so sold to be
                            earmarked at Federal Reserve Bank, New York in the name of Bank Mellie
                            Iran.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Berle</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>